dc:source  a    owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_5296  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: overexpression of GFP-Rac3 showed localization to dendritic shaft and spines (co-localizatoin with endogenous Homer) in 4DIV hippocampal neurons.\n\nFigure 4: double knockout of Rac1 and Rac3 leads to severely impaired postsynapse formation in 4DIV hippocampal neurons, which could be rescued by overexpression of either GFP-Rac3 or GFP-Rac1.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 3 legend: \"WT mouse hippocampal neurons transfected at DIV4 with plasmids for GFP (upper panels) or GFP-Rac3 (lower panels) were fixed at DIV14 and immunostained with antibodies specific for GFP (green), presynaptic marker VAMP2 (blue), and postsynaptic marker Homer (red).\"\n\nThe overexpressed Rac3 sequence was also from mouse (i.e. authors knockdown Rac1 and Rac3 in Figure 4 and then overexpress either Rac for partial rescue of the spine-formation phenotype)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5296" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

